                            <comment id="14152747" author="decster" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 02:52:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Chris, which problem when build using cmake 2.6? I am using cmake 2.8 and macos10.9, and can build current trunk successfully.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14152788" author="cnauroth" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 04:43:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, Binglin.  Please see my prior comment for a link to the relevant CMake bug.  I&apos;m on OS X 10.9.4 and running Oracle JDK 1.7.0_67.  The package places jni_md.h under a &quot;darwin&quot; sub-directory:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; tree $JAVA_HOME/include
/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_67.jdk/Contents/Home/include
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; classfile_constants.h
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; darwin
&#9474;&#160;&#160; &#9500;&#9472;&#9472; jawt_md.h
&#9474;&#160;&#160; &#9492;&#9472;&#9472; jni_md.h
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; jawt.h
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; jdwpTransport.h
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; jni.h
&#9500;&#9472;&#9472; jvmti.h
&#9492;&#9472;&#9472; jvmticmlr.h

1 directory, 8 files
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix in CMake 3.0 was to change FindJNI.cmake to look under the darwin sub-directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll hold off on committing this until tomorrow.  Let me know if you think I&apos;m missing anything.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14152814" author="decster" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 05:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ooh, java1.7 I&apos;m currently using java1.6 so that&apos;s why cmake2.8 works for me. Thanks for the explanation, please commit. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153293" author="cnauroth" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 15:38:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the reviews, Allen and Binglin.  I committed this to trunk and branch-2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
